obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (35411)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35411&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Hotel-Receipts Tax Act, 1980.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (35412)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35412&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(1) "assessee" means a person by whom hotel-receipts tax or any other sum of money is payable`
  line `under this Act and includes--`
  line
  line `(a) every person in respect of whom any proceeding under this Act has been taken for the`
  line `assessment of his chargeable receipts or of the amount of refund due to him or of the chargeable`
  line `receipts of any other person in respect of which he is assessable or of the amount of refund due to`
  line `such other person;`
  line
  line `(b) every person who is deemed to be an assessee in default under any provision of this Act;`
  line
  line `(2) "assessment" includes reassessment;`
  line
  line `(3) "assessment year" means the period of twelve months commencing on the 1st day of April`
  line `every year;`
  line
  line `(4) "Board" means the Central Board of Direct Taxes constituted under the Central Boards of`
  line `Revenue Act, 1963 (54 of 1963);`
  line
  line `(5) "chargeable receipts" means the total amount of all charges referred to in section 6, computed`
  line `in the manner laid down in section 7;`
  line
  line `(6) "hotel" includes a building or part of a building where residential accommodation is, by way`
  line `of business, provided for a monetary consideration;`
  line
  line `(7) "hotel-receipts tax" or "tax" means the tax chargeable under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(8) "Income-tax Act" means the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961);`
  line
  line `(9) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(10) "room charges" means the charges for a unit of residential accommodation in a hotel and`
  line `includes the charges for`
  line
  line `(a) furniture, air-conditioner, refrigerator, radio, music, telephone, television, and`
  line
  line `(b) such other services as are normally included by a hotel in room rent,`
  line
  line `but does not include charges for food, drink and any services other than those referred to in`
  line `sub-clauses (a) and (b);`
  line
  line `(11) all other words and expressions used herein but not defined and defined in the Income-tax`
  line `Act shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (35413)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Application of the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35413&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2) and sub-section (3), this`
  line `Act shall apply in relation to every hotel wherein the room charges for residential accommodation`
  line `provided to any person at any time during the previous year are seventy-five rupees or more per day per`
  line individual.
  line
  line `Explanation.-- Where the room charges are payable otherwise than on daily basis or per individual,`
  line `then the room charges shall be computed as for a day and per individual based on the period of`
  line `occupation of the residential accommodation for which the charges are payable and the number of individuals ordinarily permitted to occupy such accommodation according to the rules and custom of the`
  line hotel.
  line
  line `(2) Where a composite charge is payable in respect of residential accommodation and food, the room`
  line `charges included therein shall be determined in the prescribed manner.`
  line
  line `(3) Where--`
  line
  line `(i) a composite charge is payable in respect of residential accommodation, food, drink and other`
  line `services, or any of them, and the case is not covered by the provisions of sub-section (2), or`
  line
  line `(ii) it appears to the Income-tax Officer that the charges for residential accommodation, food,`
  line `drink or other services are so arranged that the room charges are understated and the other charges are`
  line overstated,
  line
  line `the Income-tax Officer shall, for the purposes of sub-section (1), determine the room charges on such`
  line `reasonable basis as he may deem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (35414)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Tax authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35414&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Director of Inspection, Commissioner of Income-Tax, Commissioner`
  line `of Income-tax (Appeals), Inspecting Assistant Commissioner of Income-tax, Income-tax Officer and`
  line `Inspector of Income-tax shall have the like powers and perform the like functions under this Act as he has`
  line `and performs under the Income-tax Act, and for the exercise of his powers and the performance of his`
  line `functions, his jurisdiction under this Act shall be the same as he has under the Income-tax Act.`
  line
  line `(2) All officers and persons employed in the execution of this Act shall observe and follow the orders,`
  line `instructions and directions of the Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such orders, instructions or directions shall be issued--`
  line
  line `(a) so as to require any tax authority to make a particular assessment or to dispose of a particular`
  line `case in a particular manner; or`
  line
  line `(b) so as to interfere with the discretion of the Commissioner (Appeals) in the exercise of his`
  line `appellate functions.`
  line
  line `(3) Every Income-tax Officer employed in the execution of this Act shall observe and follow the`
  line `orders, instructions and directions issued for his guidance by the Director of Inspection or by the`
  line `Commissioner or by the Inspecting Assistant Commissioner within whose jurisdiction he performs his`
  line functions.
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (35415)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Charge of tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35415&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, there shall be charged on every person`
  line `carrying on the business of a hotel in relation to which this Act applies, for every assessment year`
  line `commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 1981, a tax in respect of his chargeable receipts of the`
  line `previous year at the rate of fifteen per cent. of such receipts:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such chargeable receipts include any charges received in foreign exchange, then,`
  line `the tax payable by the assessee shall be reduced by an amount equal to five per cent. of the charges`
  line `(exclusive of the amounts payable by way of sales tax, entertainment tax, tax on luxuries or tax under this`
  line `Act) so received in foreign exchange.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section,--`
  line
  line `(a) charges received in Indian currency obtained by conversion of foreign exchange into Indian`
  line `currency shall, in such cases and in such circumstances as may be prescribed, be deemed to have been`
  line `received in foreign exchange; and`
  line
  line `(b) "foreign exchange" and "Indian currency" shall have the meanings respectively assigned to`
  line `them in clauses (h) and (k) of section 2 of the Foreign Exchange Regulation Act, 1973 (46 of 1973).`
  line
  line `(2) Where, under an arrangement made between a person carrying on the business of a hotel to which`
  line `this Act applies and any other person having close connection with him, any food, drink or other services`
  line `is or are provided on the premises of such hotel by the second-mentioned person and the Income-tax`
  line `Officer is of opinion that such arrangement has been made with a view to avoiding or reducing the`
  line `liability under this Act by the first-mentioned person, then,--`
  line
  line `(a) the second-mentioned person shall also be deemed to be a person carrying on the business of a`
  line `hotel to which this Act applies; and`
  line
  line `(b) hotel-receipts tax shall be charged on the second-mentioned person in respect of charges for`
  line `food, drink or other services so provided by him as if such charges were the chargeable receipts of the`
  line `business of a hotel deemed to be carried on by him under clause (a), and all the provisions of this Act`
  line `shall apply accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this sub-section,--`
  line
  line `(i) a close connection shall be deemed to exist between a person carrying on the business of a`
  line `hotel and another person if, in relation to the person carrying on the business of a hotel, such`
  line `other person is a person referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 40A of the`
  line `Income-tax Act;`
  line
  line `(ii) any food, drink or other service shall be deemed to have been provided on the premises of`
  line `a hotel if the same is or are provided in the hotel or any place appurtenant thereto and where the`
  line `hotel is situate in a part of building, in any other part of the building.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (35416)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Scope of chargeable receipts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 14 of 1982, s. 41 (w.e.f. 1-4-1982).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35416&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the chargeable receipts of`
  line `any previous year of an assessee shall be the total amount of all charges, by whatever name called,`
  line `received by, or accruing or arising to, the assessee in connection with the provision of residential`
  line `accommodation, food, drink and other services or any of them (including such charges from persons not`
  line `provided with such accommodation ^1[but excluding such charges from persons within the purview of the`
  line `Vienna Convention on Diplomatic Relations, 1961 or the Vienna Convention on Consular Relations,`
  line `1963]) in the course of carrying on the business of a hotel to which this Act applies and shall also include`
  line `every amount collected by the assessee by way of tax under this Act, sales tax, entertainment tax and tax`
  line `on luxuries.`
  line
  line `(2) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that where any such charges have been included in`
  line `the chargeable receipts of any previous year as charges accruing or arising to the assessee during that`
  line `previous year, such charges shall not be included in the chargeable receipts of any subsequent previous`
  line `year in which they are received by the assessee.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (35417)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Computation of chargeable receipts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 14 of 1982, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1-4-1982).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35417&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), the`
  line `following deductions shall be allowed in computing the chargeable receipts of any previous year--`
  line
  line `(i) the amount of charges accruing or arising in an earlier previous year which is established to`
  line `have become a bad debt during the previous year:`
  line
  line `Provided that such charges have been taken into account in computing the chargeable receipts of`
  line `the assessee of any earlier previous year and the amount has been written off as irrecoverable in the`
  line `accounts of the assessee for the previous year during which it is established to have become a bad`
  line debt;
  line
  line `(ii) any amount payable by way of sales tax, entertainment tax or tax on luxuries in respect of any`
  line `charges included in the chargeable receipts of the previous year;`
  line
  line `(iii) the amount of tax chargeable under this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that in computing the chargeable`
  line `receipts of a previous year, no deduction, other than the deductions specified in this sub-section, shall be`
  line `allowed from the total amount of charges received by, or accruing or arising to, the assessee.`
  line
  line `(2) In computing the chargeable receipts of a previous year, the amount of charges which is received`
  line `by or which accrues or arises to the assessee before the expiry of one month from the end of the month in`
  line `which this Act comes into force ^1[or after the 27th day of February, 1982] shall not be taken into account.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (35418)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Return of chargeable receipts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35418&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person, who, during the previous year, carried on the`
  line `business of a hotel in relation to which this Act applies or is assessable in respect of the chargeable`
  line `receipts of any other person under this Act, shall furnish a return of his chargeable receipts or the`
  line `chargeable receipts of such other person of the previous year in the prescribed form and verified in the`
  line `prescribed manner and setting forth such other particulars as may be prescribed, before the expiry of four`
  line `months from the end of the previous year in respect of the business of the hotel or where there is more`
  line `than one previous year in respect of such business, from the end of the previous year which expired last`
  line `before the commencement of the assessment year, or before the 30th day of June of the assessment year,`
  line `whichever is later:`
  line
  line `Provided that, on an application made in this behalf, the Income- tax Officer may, in his discretion,`
  line `extend the date for furnishing the return.`
  line
  line `(2) In the case of any person who, in the Income-tax Officer's opinion is assessable under this Act,`
  line `whether in respect of his own chargeable receipts or in respect of the chargeable receipts of any other`
  line `person, the Income-tax Officer may, before the end of the relevant assessment year, issue a notice to him`
  line `and serve the same upon him, requiring him to furnish within thirty days from the date of service of the`
  line `notice a return of his chargeable receipts or the chargeable receipts of such other person of the previous`
  line `year in the prescribed form and verified in the prescribed manner and setting forth such other particulars`
  line `as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that on an application made in this behalf, the Income-tax Officer may, in his discretion,`
  line `extend the date for furnishing the return.`
  line
  line `(3) Any assessee who has not furnished a return within the time allowed under sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (2), or having furnished a return under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), discovers any`
  line `omission or wrong statement therein, may furnish a return or a revised return, as the case may be, at any`
  line `time before the assessment is made.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (35419)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title Self-assessment.
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35419&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any hotel-receipts tax is payable on the basis of any return required`
  line `to be furnished under section 8 or section 13 after taking into account the amount of hotel-receipts tax, if`
  line `any, already paid under any provision of this Act, the assessee shall be liable to pay such tax before`
  line `furnishing the return and the return shall be accompanied by proof of payment of such tax.`
  line
  line `(2) After an assessment under section 10 or section 11 has been made, any amount paid under`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be deemed to have been paid towards such assessment.`
  line
  line `(3) If any assessee fails to pay the hotel-receipts tax or any part thereof in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (1), the Income-tax Officer may direct that a sum equal to two per cent. of such`
  line `tax or part thereof, as the case may be, shall be recovered from him by way of penalty for every month`
  line `during which the default continues:`
  line
  line `Provided that before levying any such penalty, the assessee shall be given a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (35420)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title Assessment.
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35420&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of making an assessment under this Act, the Income-tax`
  line `Officer may serve on any person who has furnished a return under section 8 or upon whom a notice has`
  line `been served under sub-section (2) of section 8 (whether a return has been furnished or not) a notice`
  line `requiring him on a date therein to be specified, to produce or cause to be produced such accounts or`
  line `documents or other evidence as the Income-tax Officer may require for the purposes of this Act and may,`
  line `from time to time, serve further notices requiring the production of such further accounts or documents or`
  line `other evidence as he may require.`
  line
  line `(2) The Income-tax Officer, after considering such accounts, documents or other evidence, if any, as`
  line `he has obtained under sub-section (1) and after taking into account any relevant material which he has gathered, shall, by an order in writing, assess the chargeable receipts and the amount of the hotel-receipts`
  line `tax payable on the basis of such assessment.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (35421)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Best judgment assessment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35421&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line --If--
  line
  line `(a) any person fails to make the return required by any notice given under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 8 and has not made a return or a revised return under sub-section (3) of that section, or`
  line
  line `(b) any person having made a return, fails to comply with all the terms of a notice issued under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 10, or`
  line
  line `(c) the Income-tax Officer is not satisfied about the correctness or the completeness of the`
  line `accounts of the assessee,`
  line
  line `the Income-tax Officer, after taking into account all relevant material which he has gathered shall make`
  line `the assessment of the chargeable receipts to the best of his judgment and determine the sum payable by`
  line `the assessee or refundable to the assessee on the basis of such assessment.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (35422)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Re-opening of assessment at the instance of the assessee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35422&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an assessee assessed`
  line `under section 11 makes an application to the Income-tax Officer, within one month from the date of`
  line `service of a notice of demand issued in consequence of the assessment, for the cancellation of the`
  line `assessment on the ground--`
  line
  line `(i) that he was prevented by sufficient cause from making the return required under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 8, or`
  line
  line `(ii) that he did not receive the notice issued under sub-section (1) of section 10, or`
  line
  line `(iii) that he had not a reasonable opportunity to comply, or was prevented by sufficient cause`
  line `from complying, with the terms of the notice referred to in clause (ii),`
  line
  line `the Income-tax Officer shall, if satisfied about the existence of such ground, cancel the assessment and`
  line `proceed to make a fresh assessment in accordance with the provisions of section 10 or section 11.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application made under sub-section (1) shall be disposed of within ninety days from the`
  line `date of receipt thereof by the Income-tax Officer:`
  line
  line `Provided that in computing the period of ninety days aforesaid, any delay in disposing of the`
  line `application which is attributable to the assessee shall be excluded.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (35423)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Receipts escaping assessment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35423&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line --If--
  line
  line `(a) the Income-tax Officer has reason to believe that by reason of the omission or failure on the`
  line `part of the assessee to make a return under section 8 for any assessment year or to disclose fully and`
  line `truly all material facts necessary for his assessment for any assessment year, chargeable receipts for`
  line `that year have escaped assessment or have been under-assessed or have been made the subject of`
  line `excessive relief under this Act, or`
  line
  line `(b) notwithstanding that there has been no omission or failure as mentioned in clause (a) on the`
  line `part of the assessee, the Income-tax Officer has, in consequence of information in his possession,`
  line `reason to believe that chargeable receipts assessable for any assessment year have escaped assessment`
  line `or have been under-assessed or have been the subject of excessive relief under this Act,`
  line
  line `he may, in cases falling under clause (a), at any time, and in cases falling under clause (b), at any time`
  line `within four years of the end of that assessment year, serve on the assessee a notice containing all or any of`
  line `the requirements which may be included in a notice under section 8 and may proceed to assess or reassess`
  line `the amount chargeable to hotel-receipts tax, and the provisions of this Act shall, so far as may be, apply,`
  line `as if the notice were a notice issued under that section.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (35424)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Advance payment of hotel receipts tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35424&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Hotel-receipts tax shall be payable in advance`
  line `during the financial year in respect of the chargeable receipts of the period which would be the previous`
  line `year for the immediately following assessment year in accordance with the provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(2) Hotel-receipts tax shall be payable in advance in two instalments on the following dates during the`
  line `financial year, namely:`
  line
  line `(i) the 15th day of September in respect of the chargeable receipts attributable to the first half of`
  line `the previous year; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the 15th day of March in respect of the chargeable receipts attributable to the second half of`
  line `the previous year:`
  line
  line `Provided that the hotel-receipts tax payable in advance during the financial year commencing on`
  line `the 1st day of April, 1980 shall be payable in one sum on the 15th day of March, 1981.`
  line
  line `(3) Every assessee shall, in each financial year, on or before such of the dates on which an instalment`
  line `of hotel-receipts tax is payable in advance, send to the Income-tax Officer, an estimate of the chargeable`
  line `receipts attributable to the relevant part of the previous year and the hotel-receipts tax payable in advance`
  line `on such chargeable receipts and shall pay such amount of hotel-receipts tax as accords with his estimate`
  line `on or before the relevant date specified in sub-section (2):`
  line
  line `Provided that in respect of the hotel-receipts tax payable in advance during the financial year`
  line `commencing on the 1st day of April, 1980, the assessee shall send to the Income-tax Officer an estimate`
  line `of the chargeable receipts attributable to the period which would be the previous year for the assessment`
  line `year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1981 and the hotel-receipts tax payable in advance on such`
  line `chargeable receipts and shall pay such amount of hotel-receipts tax as accords with his estimate on or`
  line `before the 15th day of March, 1981.`
  line
  line `(4) Every estimate under this section shall be sent in the prescribed form and verified in the`
  line `prescribed manner.`
  line
  line `(5) If any assessee does not pay on or before the specified date any instalment of hotel-receipts tax`
  line `payable in advance, he shall be deemed to be an assessee in default in respect of such instalment.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (35425)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Penalty for failure to furnish returns, comply with notices, concealment of receipts, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35425&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `If, in the course of any proceedings under this Act, the Income-tax Officer or the Commissioner (Appeals)`
  line `is satisfied that any person--`
  line
  line `(a) has, without reasonable cause, failed to furnish the return of chargeable receipts which he was`
  line `required to furnish under sub-section (1) of section 8 or by notice given under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 8 or section 13 or has, without reasonable cause, failed to furnish it within the time allowed`
  line `and the manner required by sub-section (1) of section 8 or by such notice, as the case may be, or`
  line
  line `(b) has, without reasonable cause, failed to comply with the notice under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 10, or`
  line
  line `(c) has concealed the particulars of his chargeable receipts or furnished inaccurate particulars of`
  line `such receipts,`
  line
  line `he may direct that such person shall pay by way of penalty,--`
  line
  line `(i) in the cases referred to in clause (a), in addition to the hotel-receipts tax payable by him, a sum`
  line `equal to two per cent. of the assessed tax for every month during which the default continued, but not`
  line `exceeding in the aggregate fifty per cent. of the assessed tax.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this clause, "assessed tax" means hotel-receipts tax chargeable under the`
  line `provisions of this Act, as reduced by the sum, if any, paid in advance under section 14;`
  line
  line `(ii) in the cases referred to in clause (b), in addition to the hotel-receipts tax payable by him, a`
  line `sum which shall not be less than ten per cent. but which shall not exceed fifty per cent. of the amount`
  line `of the hotel-receipts tax which would have been avoided if the return made by him had been accepted`
  line `as correct;`
  line
  line `(iii) in the cases referred to in clause (c), in addition to the hotel-receipts tax payable by him, a`
  line `sum which shall not be less than, but which shall not exceed twice, the amount of hotel-receipts tax`
  line `which would have been avoided if the return made by him had been accepted as correct:`
  line
  line `Provided that in a case falling under clause (c), the Income-tax Officer shall not impose any penalty`
  line `without the previous approval of the Inspecting Assistant Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(2) On making an order imposing a penalty under this section, the Commissioner (Appeals) shall`
  line `forthwith send a copy of the same to the Income-tax Officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (35426)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Penality for false estimate of, or failure to pay, hotel-receipts tax payable in advance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35426&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `If, in`
  line `the course of any proceedings in connection with the assessment under section 10 or section 11, the`
  line `Income-tax Officer is satisfied that any assessee--`
  line
  line `(a) has furnished under section 14, an estimate of the hotel-receipts tax payable in advance by`
  line `him which he knew or had reason to believe to be untrue, or`
  line
  line `(b) has, without reasonable cause, failed to furnish an estimate of the hotel-receipts tax payable in`
  line `advance by him in accordance with the provisions of section 14,`
  line
  line `he may direct that the assessee shall, in addition to the hotel-receipts tax payable by him, pay by way of`
  line `penalty a sum--`
  line
  line `(i) which, in the case referred to in clause (a), shall not be less than ten per cent. but shall not`
  line `exceed one and a half times the amount by which the hotel-receipts tax paid in advance during the`
  line `financial year immediately preceding the assessment year, falls short of eighty-five per cent. of the`
  line `hotel-receipts tax chargeable under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(ii) which, in the case referred to in clause (b), shall not be less than ten per cent. but shall not`
  line `exceed one and a half times of eighty-five per cent. of the hotel-receipts tax chargeable under the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (35427)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Opportunity of being heard.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35427&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `No order imposing penalty under section 15 or section 16 shall`
  line `be made unless the assessee has been heard, or has been given a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (35428)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Appeals to the Commissioner (Appeals).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35428&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person objecting to the amount of`
  line `hotel-receipts tax for which he is assessed by the Income-tax Officer, or denying his liablility to be`
  line `assessed under this Act, or objecting to an order under section 12 refusing to re-open an assessment made`
  line `under section 11 or objecting to any penalty or fine imposed by the Income-tax Officer, or to the amount`
  line `allowed by the Income-tax Officer by way of any relief under any provision of this Act, or to any refusal`
  line `by the Income-tax Officer to grant relief, or to an order of rectification having the effect of enhancing the`
  line `assessment or reducing the refund, or to an order refusing to allow the claim made by the assessee for a`
  line `rectification under section 20, may appeal to the Commissioner (Appeals).`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal shall be in the prescribed form and shall be verified in the prescribed manner.`
  line
  line `(3) An appeal shall be presented within thirty days of the following date, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) where the appeal relates to assessment or penalty or fine, the date of service of the notice of`
  line `demand relating to the assessment or penalty or fine, or`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, the date on which the intimation of the order sought to be appealed against`
  line `is served:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commissioner (Appeals) may admit an appeal after the expiration of the said period`
  line `if he is satisfied that the appellant had sufficient cause for not presenting it within that period.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commissioner (Appeals) shall hear and determine the appeal and, subject to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, pass such orders as he thinks fit and such orders may include an order enhancing the assessment`
  line `or penalty:`
  line
  line `Provided that an order enhancing the assessment or penalty shall not be made unless the person`
  line `affected thereby has been given a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against such enhancement.`
  line
  line `(5) The procedure to be adopted in the hearing and determination of the appeals shall, with any`
  line `necessary modification, be in accordance with the procedure applicable in relation to income-tax.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (35429)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Appeals to Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 16 of 1981, s. 45, for "one hundred and twenty-five rupees" (w.e.f. 1-6-1981).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35429&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any assessee aggrieved by an order passed by a`
  line `Commissioner under section 22, or an order passed by a Commissioner (Appeals) under any provision of`
  line `this Act, may appeal to the Appellate Tribunal against such order.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner may, if he objects to any order passed by the Commissioner (Appeals) under`
  line `any provision of this Act, direct the Income-tax Officer to appeal to the Appellate Tribunal against the`
  line order.
  line
  line `(3) Every appeal under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall be filed within sixty days of the date`
  line `on which the order sought to be appealed against is communicated to the assessee or to the`
  line `Commissioner, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) The Income-tax Officer or the assessee, as the case may be, on receipt or a notice that an appeal`
  line `against the order of the Commissioner (Appeals) has been preferred under sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (2) by the other party may, notwithstanding that he may not have appealed against such order`
  line `or any part thereof, within thirty days of the receipt of the notice, file a memorandum of cross-objections,`
  line `verified in the prescribed manner, against any part of the order of the Commissioner (Appeals), and such`
  line `memorandum shall be disposed of by the Appellate Tribunal as if it were an appeal presented within the`
  line `time specified in sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) The Appellate Tribunal may admit an appeal or permit the filing of a memorandum of crossobjections after the expiry of the relevant period referred to in sub-section (3) or sub-section (4), if it is`
  line `satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not presenting it within that period.`
  line
  line `(6) An appeal to the Appellate Tribunal shall be in the prescribed form and shall be verified in the`
  line `prescribed manner and shall, except in the case of an appeal referred to in sub-section (2) or a`
  line `memorandum of cross-objections referred to in sub-section (4), be accompanied by a fee of ^1[two hundred`
  line rupees].
  line
  line `(7) Subject to the provisions of this Act, in hearing and making an order on any appeal under this`
  line `section, the Appellate Tribunal shall exercise the same powers and follow the same procedure as it`
  line `exercises and follows in hearing and making an order on any appeal under the Income-tax Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (35430)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Rectification of mistakes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35430&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) With a view to rectifying any mistake apparent from the record,`
  line `the Income-tax Officer, the Commissioner (Appeals), the Commissioner and the Appellate Tribunal may,`
  line `of his or its own motion or on an application by the assessee in this behalf, or where the authority`
  line `concerned is the Commissioner (Appeals), by the Income-tax Officer also, amend any order passed by`
  line `him or it in any proceeding under this Act within four years of the date on which such order was passed.`
  line
  line `(2) An amendment which has the effect of enhancing the assessment or reducing a refund or`
  line `otherwise increasing the liability of the assessee shall not be made under this section unless the authority`
  line `concerned has given notice to the assessee of its intention so to do and has allowed the assessee a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an amendment is made under this section, the order shall be passed in writing by the`
  line `authority concerned.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, where any such amendment has the effect of reducing`
  line `the assessment, the Income-tax Officer shall make any refund which may be due to such assessee.`
  line
  line `(5) Where any such amendment has the effect of enhancing the assessment or reducing the refund`
  line `already made, the Income-tax Officer shall serve on the assessee a notice of demand in the prescribed`
  line `form specifying the sum payable.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (35431)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Hotel-receipts tax deductible in computing total income under Income-tax Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35431&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Income-tax Act, in computing the income chargeable to`
  line `income-tax under the head Profits and gains of business or profession in the case of an assessee`
  line `carrying on the business of a hotel to which this Act applies, the hotel-receipts tax payable by the assessee for any assessment year shall be deductible from the profits and gains of the business of the hotel`
  line `assessable for that assessment year.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (35432)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Revision of order prejudicial to revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35432&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner may call for and examine the`
  line `record of any proceeding under this Act and if he considers that any order passed therein by the`
  line `Income-tax Officer is erroneous in so far as it is prejudicial to the interests of the revenue, he may, after`
  line `giving the assessee an opportunity of being heard and after making or causing to be made such enquiry as`
  line `he deems necessary, pass such order thereon as the circumstances of the case justify, including an order`
  line `enhancing or modifying the assessment, or cancelling the assessment and directing a fresh assessment.`
  line
  line `(2) No order shall be made under sub-section (1)--`
  line
  line `(a) to revise an order of reassessment made under section 13, or`
  line
  line `(b) after the expiry of two years from the date of the order sought to be revised.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), an order in revision under this section may`
  line `be passed at any time in the case of an order which has been passed in consequence of, or to give effect`
  line `to, any finding or direction contained in an order of the Appellate Tribunal, the High Court or the`
  line `Supreme Court.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- In computing the period of limitation for the purposes of sub-section (2), any period`
  line `during which any proceeding under this section is stayed by an order or injunction of any court shall be`
  line excluded.
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (35433)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Revision of orders by Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35433&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner may, either of his own motion or`
  line `on an application by the assessee for revision, call for the record of any proceeding under this Act which`
  line `has been taken by an Income-tax Officer subordinate to him and may make such enquiry or cause such`
  line `enquiry to be made and, subject to the provisions of this Act, may pass such order thereon, not being an`
  line `order prejudicial to the assessee, as he thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner shall not of his own motion revise any order under this section if the order has`
  line `been made more than one year previously.`
  line
  line `(3) In the case of an application for revision under this section by the assessee, the application shall be`
  line `made within one year from the date on which the order in question was communicated to him or the date`
  line `on which he otherwise came to know of it, whichever is earlier:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commissioner may, if he is satisfied that the assessee was prevented by sufficient`
  line `cause from making the application within that period, admit an application made after the expiry of that`
  line period.
  line
  line `(4) The Commissioner shall not revise any order under this section in the following cases:--`
  line
  line `(a) where an appeal against the order lies to the Commissioner (Appeals) but has not been made`
  line `and the time within which such appeal may be made has not expired, or the assessee has not waived`
  line `his right of appeal; or`
  line
  line `(b) where the order has been made the subject of an appeal to the Commissioner (Appeals).`
  line
  line `(5) Every application by an assessee for revision under this section shall be accompanied by a fee of`
  line `twenty-five rupees.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- An order by the Commissioner declining to interfere shall, for the purposes of this`
  line `section, be deemed not to be an order prejudicial to the assessee.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (35434)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Application of provisions of Income-tax Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35434&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of the following sections and`
  line `Schedules of the Income-tax Act and the Income-tax (Certificate Proceedings) Rules, 1962, as in force`
  line `from time to time, shall apply with necessary modifications as if the said provisions and the rules referred`
  line `to hotel-receipts tax instead of to income-tax:--`
  line
  line `2(43B) and (44), 41(4), 118, 125, 125A, 128 to 136 (both inclusive), 138, 140, 144A, 156, 159 to`
  line `163 (both inclusive), 166, 167, 170, 171, 173 to 179 (both inclusive), 187, 188, 189, 219 to 227 (both`
  line `inclusive), 228A, 229, 231, 232, 237 to 242 (both inclusive), 244, 245, 254 to 262 (both inclusive), 265, 266, 268, 269, 278B, 278C, 278D, 281, 281B, 282, 283, 284, 287, 288, 288A, 288B, 289 to 293`
  line `(both inclusive), the Second Schedule and the Third Schedule:`
  line
  line `Provided that references in the said provisions and the rules to the assessee shall be construed as`
  line `references to an assessee as defined in this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (35435)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Income-tax papers to be available for the purposes of this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35435&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in the Income-tax Act, all information contained in any statement or return made or furnished`
  line `under the provisions of that Act or obtained or collected for the purposes of that Act may be used for the`
  line `purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) All information contained in any statement or return made on furnished under the provisions of`
  line `this Act or obtained or collected for the purposes of this Act may be used for the purposes of the Incometax Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (35436)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Wilful attempt to evade tax, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35436&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a person wilfully attempts in any manner whatsoever to`
  line `evade any tax, penalty or interest chargeable or imposable under this Act, he shall, without prejudice to`
  line `any penalty that may be imposable on him under any other provision of this Act, be punishable,--`
  line
  line `(i) in a case where the amount sought to be evaded exceeds one hundred thousand rupees, with`
  line `rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six months but which may extend to`
  line `seven years and with fine;`
  line
  line `(ii) in any other case, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three`
  line `months but which may extend to three years and with fine.`
  line
  line `(2) If a person wilfully attempts in any manner whatsoever to evade the payment of any tax, penalty`
  line `or interest under this Act, he shall, without prejudice to any penalty that may be imposable on him under`
  line `any other provision of this Act, be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be`
  line `less than three months but which may extend to three years and shall, in the discretion of the court, also`
  line `be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, a wilful attempt to evade any tax, penalty or interest`
  line `chargeable or imposable under this Act or the payment thereof shall include a case where any person--`
  line
  line `(i) has in his possession or control any books of account or other documents (being books of`
  line `account or other documents relevant to any proceeding under this Act) containing a false entry or`
  line `statement; or`
  line
  line `(ii) makes or causes to be made any false entry or statement in such books of account or other`
  line `documents; or`
  line
  line `(iii) wilfully omits or causes to be omitted any relevant entry or statement in such books of`
  line `account or other documents; or`
  line
  line `(iv) causes any other circumstance to exist which will have the effect of enabling such person to`
  line `evade any tax, penalty or interest chargeable or imposable under this Act or the payment thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (35437)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Failure to furnish returns of chargeable receipts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35437&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `If a person wilfully fails to furnish in due`
  line `time the return of chargeable receipts which he is required to furnish under sub-section (1) of section 8 or`
  line `by notice given under sub-section (2) of section 8 or section 13, he shall be punishable,--`
  line
  line `(i) in a case where the amount of tax, which would have been evaded if the failure had not been`
  line `discovered, exceeds one hundred thousand rupees, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall`
  line `not be less than six months but which may extend to seven years and with fine;`
  line
  line `(ii) in any other case, with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three months but`
  line `which may extend to three years and with fine:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person shall not be proceeded against under this section for failure to furnish in due`
  line `time the return of chargeable receipts under sub-section (1) of section 8, if--`
  line
  line `(a) the return is furnished by him before the expiry of the assessment year; or`
  line
  line `(b) the tax payable by him on the chargeable receipts determined on assessment as reduced by the`
  line `tax paid in advance under section 14, if any, does not exceed three thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (35438)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Failure to produce accounts and documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35438&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `If a person wilfully fails to produce, or cause to`
  line `be produced, on or before the date specified in any notice served on him under sub-section (1) of section`
  line `10, such accounts and documents as are referred to in the notice, he shall be punishable with rigorous`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine equal to a sum calculated at a rate`
  line `which shall not be less than four rupees or more than ten rupees for every day during which the default`
  line `continues, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (35439)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `False statement in verification, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35439&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `If a person makes a statement in any verification under`
  line `this Act or under any rule made thereunder, or delivers an account or statement which is false, and which`
  line `he either knows or believes to be false, or does not believe to be true, he shall be punishable,--`
  line
  line `(i) in a case where the amount of tax, which would have been evaded if the statement or account`
  line `had been accepted as true, exceeds one hundred thousand rupees, with rigorous imprisonment for a`
  line `term which shall not be less than six months but which may extend to seven years and with fine;`
  line
  line `(ii) in any other case, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three`
  line `months but which may extend to three years and with fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (35440)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Abetment of false return, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35440&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `If a person abets or induces in any manner another person to`
  line `make and deliver an account or a statement or declaration relating to any chargeable receipts which is`
  line `false and which he either knows to be false or does not believe to be true or to commit an offence under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 26, he shall be punishable,--`
  line
  line `(i) in a case where the amount of tax, penalty or interest which would have been evaded, if the`
  line `declaration, account or statement had been accepted as true, or which is wilfully attempted to be`
  line `evaded, exceeds one hundred thousand rupees, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not`
  line `be less than six months but which may extend to seven years and with fine;`
  line
  line `(ii) in any other case, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three`
  line `months but which may extend to three years and with fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (35441)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Punishment for second and subsequent offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35441&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `If any person convicted of an offence under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 26 or section 27 or section 29 or section 30 is again convicted for an offence`
  line `under any of the aforesaid provisions, he shall be punishable for the second and for every subsequent`
  line `offence with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six months but which may`
  line `extend to seven years and with fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (35442)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Certain offences to be non-cognizable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35442&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), an offence punishable under section 26 or section 27 or section 29`
  line `or section 30 shall be deemed to be non-cognizable within the meaning of that Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (35443)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Institution of proceedings and composition of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35443&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall not be proceeded`
  line `against for any offence under section 26 or section 27 or section 28 or section 29 or section 30 for any`
  line `offence under the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) relating to any matter connected with or arising out of`
  line `this Act, except at the instance of the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner may, either before or after the institution of proceedings, compound any`
  line `offence punishable under section 26 or section 27 or section 28 or section 29 or section 30.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (35444)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35444&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, subject to the control of the Central Government, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which the room charges may be determined under sub-section (2) of section 3`
  line `in cases where composite charges are payable in respect of residential accommodation and food;`
  line
  line `(b) the cases and the circumstances in which payments made in Indian currency by conversion of`
  line `foreign exchange into Indian currency shall be deemed to have been made in foreign exchange for the`
  line `purposes of sub-section (1) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(c) the form in which returns under section 8 may be furnished, the manner in which they may be`
  line `verified and the other particulars which a form may contain;`
  line
  line `(d) the form in which an estimate under section 14 may be sent and the manner in which it may`
  line `be verified;`
  line
  line `(e) the form in which appeals under section 18 or section 19 may be filed and the manner in`
  line `which they may be verified;`
  line
  line `(f) the form in which a memorandum of cross-objections under sub-section (4) of section 19 may`
  line `be verified;`
  line
  line `(g) the procedure to be followed on applications for rectification of mistakes under section 20;`
  line
  line `(h) the form in which a notice of demand may be served on the assessee under sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 20;`
  line
  line `(i) any other matter which by this Act is to be or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The power to make rules conferred by this section shall on the first occasion of the exercise`
  line `thereof include the power to give retrospective effect to the rules or any of them from a date not earlier`
  line `than the date of commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall cause every rule made under this section to be laid, as soon as may`
  line `be, after it is made before each House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of`
  line `the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (35445)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Power to exempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35445&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `Where the Central Government is of the opinion that it is necessary or`
  line `expedient so to do either in the public interest or having regard to the peculiar circumstances of the case,`
  line `it may, by notification in the Official Gazette and subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in`
  line `the notification, exempt any hotel or any class of hotels from the levy of hotel-receipts tax.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (35446)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35446&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, remove the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (35447)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title [Repealed].
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468&sectionId=35447&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00034_198054_1517807326468
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `[Consequential amendments].-- Rep. by the Repealing and Amending Act, 1988 (19 of 1988), s. 2`
  line `and the First Schedule (w.e.f. 31-3-1988)`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
